text: Protesters in Paris have defied a large gatherings ban imposed in response to COVID-19 to rally in front of the U.S. Embassy. It's one of several demonstrations in cities around the world against racism and in support of U.S. protesters https://t.co/LT6V4dCiwp

The U.S. Marines have issued a directive ordering the removal of all public displays of the Confederate flag in a ban that includes bumper stickers, posters, mugs, posters and clothing

name: axios
text: UPDATE: New Zealand has gone 16 days without reporting a single new coronavirus case, the Ministry of Health has said. Only 1 person in the entire country has the virus and they are not in hospital https://t.co/rrsZx6VpLn

text:
UPDATE: Seattle police set off flash bangs at a protest in the city tonight, a day after the city's Mayor Jenny Durkan announced a 30-day ban on the use of tear gas, per the Seattle Times
